<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They returned to This Morning on Tuesday for the first time since their summer holidays and Holly Willoughby's 14-day quarantine. </p>

<p>And she and co-host Phillip Schofield, 58, enjoyed their first Covid-friendly hug using a plastic screen with in-built sleeves as they reunited. </p>

<p>Their get-together comes after Holly, 39, had to cut her seven-week family holiday to Portugal short so she could quarantine to be ready to return to the show in time. </p>

<p>Safe: Holly Willoughby and Phillip Schofield used a plastic screen with sleeves to have their first hug in six months as they returned to This Morning on Tuesday following the holidays</p>

<p>Taking no chances: Their get-together comes after Holly had to cut her seven-week family holiday to Portugal short so she could quarantine to be ready to return to the show in time</p>

<p>The pair were wearing face-masks with their own faces on them at the start of the show and couldn't get over how weird they looked.  </p>

<p>Holly said: 'Don’t adjust your TV sets, there is nothing wrong, we are just wearing masks with our faces on</p>

<p>Phil laughed and said: 'Holly: the best ones are if you have a photo taken of your teeth.'</p>

<p>Doing her bit: Holly cut short her family trip to Portugal to quarantine and be back in time for work and said: 'I've just got out of quarantine so I feel a bit like "wow there's people around'</p>

<p>Happy news: Using the screen, Holly and Phil noted it had been six months since they were last able to safely embrace</p>

